      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>garam masala</strong>,<strong> ground</strong> <strong>cumin</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> chopped ginger </strong>and cook for 1 min</p>",
